refsect2.programlisting:
void                gtk_window_set_wmclass              (GtkWindow *window,
                                                         const gchar *wmclass_name,
                                                         const gchar *wmclass_class);

refsect2.para:
The basic ugly truth of this function is that it should be simply:
void gtk_window_set_resizable (GtkWindow* window, gboolean setting);
...which is why GTK+ 2.0 introduces gtk_window_set_resizable(), which you should use instead of gtk_window_set_policy().

